  "texts": [
    "The main objectives of this research are listed below,• Develop a method that effectively reduces the impact of extreme values on prediction error, even when the occurrence of such extreme values is relatively sparse in comparison to normal values within the time series.• In an unique effort normal time series values are being estimated using the sequence learning model LSTM and times series with extreme events are being modeled by the transformer.",
    "• Through an extensive series of experiments on real-world datasets, we demonstrate that the proposed model delivers high accuracy in predicting extreme events and performs comparably to leading state-of-the-art time series forecasting models.",
    "• It is also shown that incorporating an extreme event classification model can significantly reduce prediction errors in extreme event forecasting tasks.The primary objectives of this research are to develop a robust prediction method that effectively mitigates the impact of extreme values on prediction errors, even when such values are scarce.",
    "This involves employing a dual modeling strategy where normal time series values are estimated using Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks, while extreme events are modeled using transformers.",
    "Extensive experiments across diverse real-world datasets will demonstrate the TXtreme framework's high accuracy in predicting extreme events, positioning it competitively among leading time series forecasting models."
  ],
